Allocate memory in advance
A trick we use very often in coding is to ‚Äútack on‚Äù values to the end of a vector or list as we iterate through something. However, this is actually very slow! If you know how long your list is going to end up, consider pre-creating that list.

do_stuff_allocate &lt;- function(reps) {
  results &lt;- vector(length = reps)
  for (i in 1:reps) {
    results[i] &lt;- i
  }
  return(results)
}

do_stuff_tackon &lt;- function(reps) {
   results &lt;- c()
  for (i in 1:reps) {
    results &lt;- c(results, i)
  }
  return(results)
}

microbenchmark::microbenchmark(
  do_stuff_allocate(1000),
  do_stuff_tackon(1000)
)

Unit: microseconds
